|accessdate = 2006-09-05}}</ref> While the group rehearsed for the ceremony, it was "considering recording something for a yet-to-be-announced charitable project," according to a post from manager Bertis Downs on R.E.M.'s [http://www.remhq.com website]. This will mark the first time Berry has worked with the band since his departure almost a decade ago.

R.E.M. was nominated for induction into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in October, 2006, in their first year of eligibility. <ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.futurerockhall.com/2007_Nominees.php
|title = The 2007 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame Nominees
|author = Future Rock Hall
|accessdate = 2006-10-28}}</ref> It was announced in January 2007 that they would be one of five artists inducted from the nine nominees.[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/6242515.stm]

